    {
      "id": "yRp7JaWWTJAb5wcMAHM11",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 887.4413795936118,
      "y": 3448.4629843654657,
      "width": 1339.16357421875,
      "height": 135,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0I",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1283723441,
      "version": 103,
      "versionNonce": 1223986143,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1766671269408,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "When the request goes to Application server there are couple of steps that\nwe need to do\n",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "When the request goes to Application server there are couple of steps that\nwe need to do\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "9OxzrIC4Jx2u4cJ29MfNa",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1019.3122677427548,
      "y": 3625.4963883979794,
      "width": 1475.603759765625,
      "height": 1845,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b0J",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1744898929,
      "version": 2470,
      "versionNonce": 1440487551,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1767367227917,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "1. We need to register the user submission in the DB with status : pending\n\nSubmission Schema -> \n    id\n    status -> Wrong Answer/Time Limit Exceeded(TLE)/ MLE\n    codeLanguage\n    CreatedAt\n    userID\n    problmeID\n\n2. Evaluate the Submission -> where this evaluation will happen\n    In Application server -> due to this is a stateless evaluation\n    server will run the code on top of multiple test cases and give \n    us the corresponding answer, first problem is to run the code\n    and compile the code\n\n    should we run the code directly on the Application server?\n    \n    running of code can't be done on immediately , think? if running\n    of problem takes lot of time we can't allow our users to wait and\n    our screen is loading and they are not able to do anything\n\n    In Leetcode suppose we are trying to submit a problem we click on the\n    submit button and we can make one more submission immediately we can \n    make 3 or more submissions simultaneoulsy as well only criteria is code \n    should be little diff.\n    \n    Moral of the story -> running and evaluating our submission can be very \n    time consuming task \n            Why -> 1 compile the code\n                     2 run the code\n                     3 Get the internal test cases\n                     4 run our code on multiple internal test cases there might be \n                            200 or more than that test cases\n                     5 run the code one by one on each test case once the output\n                        of each test case comes up then we have to match the output \n                        of each input test case with the output test case\n                     6 based on that we have to create evaluation result\n                     7 then show to user \n\n            ",
      "fontSize": 36,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "1. We need to register the user submission in the DB with status : pending\n\nSubmission Schema -> \n    id\n    status -> Wrong Answer/Time Limit Exceeded(TLE)/ MLE\n    codeLanguage\n    CreatedAt\n    userID\n    problmeID\n\n2. Evaluate the Submission -> where this evaluation will happen\n    In Application server -> due to this is a stateless evaluation\n    server will run the code on top of multiple test cases and give \n    us the corresponding answer, first problem is to run the code\n    and compile the code\n\n    should we run the code directly on the Application server?\n    \n    running of code can't be done on immediately , think? if running\n    of problem takes lot of time we can't allow our users to wait and\n    our screen is loading and they are not able to do anything\n\n    In Leetcode suppose we are trying to submit a problem we click on the\n    submit button and we can make one more submission immediately we can \n    make 3 or more submissions simultaneoulsy as well only criteria is code \n    should be little diff.\n    \n    Moral of the story -> running and evaluating our submission can be very \n    time consuming task \n            Why -> 1 compile the code\n                     2 run the code\n                     3 Get the internal test cases\n                     4 run our code on multiple internal test cases there might be \n                            200 or more than that test cases\n                     5 run the code one by one on each test case once the output\n                        of each test case comes up then we have to match the output \n                        of each input test case with the output test case\n                     6 based on that we have to create evaluation result\n                     7 then show to user \n\n            ",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
